Joseph Wynn (wynn@next.duq.edu) wrote:

: I am implementing DES.  I am having a problem.  Since you read in data in a block of 8 characters (64 bits), what 
: do you do when you get to the end of the file and you have less than 8 characters to read in?

: Any help would be appreciated.

: Thanks,

: Joe

Sun's approach is to reserve the last byte of the last block 
to hold the number of valid data bytes in that block.
If the input is a multiple of 8 bytes, then an additional
block is appended to the output.  This last block, when
decrypted, has a 0 in the last byte.  
/mrr
